OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5F'Strong r' in danger of    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdisappearing, study finds  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The "strong r" sound at the end of     
OL,6, words may be disappearing across the   
OL,7, North of England, a study has found.   
OL,9,FLancaster University (LU) researchers  
OL,10,Fsaid rhotic speakers, who pronounce "r"
OL,11,Fsounds in words like car, her and bird,
OL,12,Fwere "becoming a thing of the past"    
OL,13,Facross the region, with one exception. 
OL,15,FDr Danielle Turton said east Lancashire
OL,16,Fhad remained an "island of rhoticity". 
OL,18,FHowever, the study lead said that even 
OL,19,Fthere, the "strong r" was in gradual   
OL,20,Fdecline among young speakers.          
